as some call them, are published
on the independent Fantagraphics
label. In case any D.C. and Marvel
fans are wondering, ‘independent
label’ means no superheroes in
tights making cliched wisecracks
as they battle formulaic threats
by forces of evil. No, on
independent labels, the artists
invite you to join them in looking
at the world from a point just
below the surface of reality. The
result is stories with a
psychological edge. And Clowes
is a master at creating stories that,
just like good horror movies,
make you laugh right before
scaring the wits out of you.

