book series from Clowes. The
first, Lloyd Llewellyn, was named
after the title character, whom
Clowes describes as a sort of “ an
Everyman character, a typical
American, addicted to all of these
things and kind of controlled by
his surroundings.”

Along with his sidekick, a
beatnik, Llewellyn finds himself
in all kinds of improbable
situations in his quest for
happiness —— even if it means
traveling to Venus to meet the
woman of his dreams and finding
out bitterly that when fantasy
meets reality, something has got
to give. In Lloyd Llewellyn, Clowes
utilized a clean, jazzy style

reminiscent of the fifties.
